Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.44,0:00:08.26,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Two more. No...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.14,0:00:13.28,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pumped.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.28,0:00:15.83,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Jota!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.70,0:00:20.61,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Jota!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.68,0:00:22.58,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.29,0:00:26.00,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,What's she doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.00,0:00:28.18,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't she watching\Nthe starting line at Otemachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.18,0:00:30.46,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.58,0:00:36.59,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.01,0:00:38.55,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,No, but—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.98,0:00:43.02,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Does she like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.05,0:00:48.02,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.14,0:01:01.99,Series_Title,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Run with the Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.25,0:02:25.49,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Bro!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.94,0:02:31.34,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.34,0:02:33.53,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,He's so strong during the actual event.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.10,0:02:39.88,main,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Joji!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:40.84,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.93,0:02:43.30,main,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.30,0:02:44.26,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.26,0:02:46.72,main,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:50.85,main,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,...she likes me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.47,0:02:55.24,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:59.74,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,What? But Hana—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:02.37,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.73,0:03:05.20,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Come here, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.33,0:03:09.79,Ep_title,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,Even If I Break
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.79,0:03:16.46,Section_4_03:09(Ep20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 4
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.52,0:03:12.80,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei is still catching up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:13.86,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Since finishing last in Section 1,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:16.07,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,their position has steadily climbed\Nto their current 10th place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.07,0:03:19.16,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, they might even\Ncatch Tokyo Sport in 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.10,0:03:21.47,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:23.88,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.42,0:03:29.85,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Did Hana herself say that she likes Jota?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.85,0:03:31.85,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:35.81,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I simply thought she liked one of the twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:38.15,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, he's suddenly assuming she does.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.15,0:03:39.53,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,He even told Joji.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.32,0:03:45.62,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would that idiot agitate\Nhis brother like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:48.67,italics,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Hana's on her way to Odawara.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.67,0:03:49.95,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is she? Godzilla?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.28,0:03:55.38,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Should we have the coach tell\Nhim Jota's confused about Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.38,0:03:57.89,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,I've never heard of that kind\Nof instruction being given before.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.89,0:03:59.45,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make the decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.85,0:04:01.09,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Not that I'm happy with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.09,0:04:03.80,Section_4(phone)_04:01(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 4
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.80,0:04:06.01,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Run, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.37,0:04:12.61,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make sense\Nthat she likes him, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:16.19,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,She was always with the two of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.19,0:04:18.44,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,When did she develop feelings for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.26,0:04:21.69,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he meant as a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:23.79,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:28.63,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,No, in that case, I like Hana as a friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:31.85,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Just as a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.28,0:04:34.88,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:42.12,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Want some help?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:45.56,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Joji, could you take out that garbage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.56,0:04:46.84,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.74,0:04:50.43,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.76,0:04:53.14,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,How can you tell us apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.14,0:04:54.39,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.03,0:04:57.78,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have think when you used my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.78,0:05:01.57,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. No one at Aotake gets you mixed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.57,0:05:02.36,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.06,0:05:05.94,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,I've never thought about\Ntrying to tell you apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.94,0:05:11.04,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,Since the day I met you,\Nyou were you, and Jota was Jota.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.71,0:05:15.45,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,You're brothers and best\Nfriends and always together,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:17.75,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,but what I like about each of you is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.16,0:05:20.40,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.40,0:05:21.21,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:23.34,flashback,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna start lighting fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:25.56,flashback,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,No way! I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.54,0:05:33.72,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Joji!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.94,0:05:37.35,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening? Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.86,0:05:39.89,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,He's really mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:42.32,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,How much did I miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.19,0:05:45.25,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.25,0:05:48.44,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure what it means, but you\Nhave a message from Kurahara.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.44,0:05:49.70,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Just listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.19,0:05:51.44,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,From Kakeru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:56.96,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,“If you like her, run.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.10,0:05:59.27,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.85,0:06:03.64,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's what I was told to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:07.65,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Who does he think he is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.33,0:06:09.13,italics,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:16.56,Location(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Odahara Relay Station
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:20.02,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,He handed me the phone. It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:22.98,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds pretty noisy over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.98,0:06:25.98,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We're all anxious to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.64,0:06:28.70,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.33,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What'd he say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.09,0:06:39.73,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,That I'd better hydrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.95,0:06:42.58,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.58,0:06:44.71,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing left to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:52.89,main,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations Takashi on\NRunning in the Hakone Ekiden
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:58.81,Certain_victory_06:54(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Certain Victory
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.13,0:07:01.44,main,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,They're almost at Section 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:02.81,main,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna run!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:11.07,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,It might not be colder than over there. Is everyone there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:11.07,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, everyone's already in front of the TV. Our uncle from Tsuruoka just arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:11.07,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei University is amazing! Yu said he's rooting for you. I'm starting to feel nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:11.07,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.78,0:07:11.07,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,First place, brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:14.03,main,PHONE,0000,0000,0000,,First place, brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:25.46,Section_4_07:17(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 4
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.62,0:07:20.35,main,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Rikudo was too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.35,0:07:23.09,main,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,The champions are slowly falling behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.54,0:07:27.13,main,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Currently in first place is Boso's Saito.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:31.45,main,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Rikudo is also within range of Daiwa in third.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.42,0:07:56.99,main,OFFICIAL,0000,0000,0000,,Saikyo is coming! Saikyo!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:07:58.95,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,I'd better go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:08:00.81,main,OFFICIAL,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo Sport is next!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.81,0:08:02.80,main,OFFICIAL,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo Sport to the relay line!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.27,0:08:05.25,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But it's Section 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.54,0:08:07.79,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, no matter the section—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.79,0:08:10.58,main,OFFICIAL,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei, Kikui! Get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.58,0:08:11.95,main,OFFICIAL,0000,0000,0000,,They're coming at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.58,0:08:13.89,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.75,0:08:16.73,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,I promise I'll make it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.66,0:08:34.22,italics,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:47.42,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.02,0:08:51.90,main,HANA,0000,0000,0000,,Joji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.05,0:08:56.30,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. What did I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.64,0:09:00.56,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't I go faster?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.60,0:09:09.31,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,He was hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:12.23,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hotter than me, and I'd just run Section 4.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.45,0:09:16.88,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.53,0:09:21.61,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I had to get us\Nas much time as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.51,0:09:23.87,main,JOJI,0000,0000,0000,,but I...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.32,0:09:25.73,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Raise your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.73,0:09:27.58,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He's already running.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.71,0:09:31.30,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,This is Car 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.30,0:09:34.51,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei's Sugiyama's pace\Nis remaining constant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.51,0:09:38.80,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kikui's Inagaki is already 500 meters ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.80,0:09:41.38,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei has suddenly hit the brakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.84,0:09:44.56,main,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:49.75,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Yokohama and Jonan Bunka\Nare catching up from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.75,0:09:52.00,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Will he be able to stay ahead of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:53.03,Tokyo-Hakone_banner_09:50(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo-Hakone Round-Trip College Ekiden Race
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.49,0:09:56.75,italics,ANALYST,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's just a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.74,0:09:57.95,Section_5_09:55(Ep20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 5
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.75,0:09:59.91,italics,ANALYST,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to be having some kind of problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.25,0:10:50.13,top,FAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei, you can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.80,0:10:51.34,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't surprise us if he stopped anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.13,0:10:52.22,top,FAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.34,0:10:55.20,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Will he be able to make it over\Nthe mountains of Hakone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:06.38,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo, go is a challenging game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.93,0:11:11.94,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,The stronger you are, the more\Nyou value the way you lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.58,0:11:17.85,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,How you recognize your loss and resign is key.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.85,0:11:23.45,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,No one blames the challenger for\Nresigning or mocks him for running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.89,0:11:28.38,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,If anything, they praise him\Nfor securing an escape route.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.04,0:11:33.38,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's because everyone knows\Nthat man was fighting to win
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.38,0:11:35.95,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,until the very end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.43,0:11:51.89,italics,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo, raise your hand if you can't keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.24,0:11:54.38,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop you immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.25,0:12:09.66,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,The lead runners are approaching\Nthe finish line at Lake Ashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.66,0:12:12.43,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Their first first-half victory in four\Nyears is right before their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.25,0:12:12.83,Tokyo-Hakone_banner_12:11(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo-Hakone Round-Trip College Ekiden Race
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.70,0:12:17.76,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,A new god has descended upon Hakone!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:23.45,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Boso second-year Yanase Wataru\Nfinishes in a new section record!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.45,0:12:26.07,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Boso wins the first half!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.50,0:12:29.89,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here with Kansei.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.89,0:12:33.57,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei's Coach Tazaki\Nhas gotten out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.57,0:12:36.94,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Will he stop Sugiyama and forfeit the race?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.02,0:12:43.11,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.59,0:12:46.82,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,He's stopped! Sugiyama has finally stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.79,0:12:53.75,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough. You did well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.03,0:13:25.53,main,SISTER,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.77,0:13:29.77,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.17,0:13:32.18,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.86,0:13:37.67,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,They're all waiting for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.06,0:13:48.76,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Why are we so desperate to keep running?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.86,0:13:55.66,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't we stop doing something\Nso painful and difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.53,0:14:00.06,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,For our friends. For our goals. For ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.63,0:14:02.05,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Stubbornness and pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.08,0:14:05.80,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. I doubt anyone knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:10.35,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we can't look away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.66,0:14:22.64,italics,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it sticks in our hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.10,0:14:53.52,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.17,0:15:04.59,Ashihara_Inn_15:00(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(314,1)}Ashihara Inn
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.95,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Kansei's Sugiyama Takashi is\Nexperiencing difficulties in Section 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:11.55,Tokyo-Hakone_banner_12:11(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo-Hakone Round-Trip College Ekiden Race
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:27.03,Hakone-Lake_Ashi15:09(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Hakone – Lake Ashi
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.95,0:15:14.71,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,While periodically stopping, he brushes\Noff his coach's attempts to stop him
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:18.28,italics,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,and finishes all 20.7 kilometers of Section 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.28,0:15:21.84,italicstop,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,Sugiyama is greeted by \Na continuous wave of cheers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:27.03,Results_15:19(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,First Half 20th – Kansei University
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:24.73,italicstop,ANNOUNCER,0000,0000,0000,,after demonstrating that he has\Nthe strongest will in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.17,0:15:29.38,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,We've already called your family.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.87,0:15:33.98,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,They said they'd come take care of you,\Nbut we politely declined their offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:43.55,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo finished his section,\Nbut tomorrow will be a difficult battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.55,0:15:44.75,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:49.67,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Because you'll run?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.01,0:15:55.58,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you're confident, but sometimes\Nmaking it to the end isn't good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.60,0:16:01.51,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow, I won't let you boys expose\Nyourselves to the same kind of danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.51,0:16:04.81,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fully prepared for tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:08.78,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Switching our focus to that comes first.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.50,0:16:11.49,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.42,0:16:14.06,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.51,0:16:20.84,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,Once you've prepared\Nfor tomorrow, call the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.84,0:16:22.04,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't yet, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:24.76,main,TAZAKI,0000,0000,0000,,They must be anxious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.44,0:16:34.25,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.50,0:16:37.97,italics,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,Nice work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.50,0:16:38.69,italics,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Shindo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.69,0:16:41.81,italics,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Musa, there's no point in getting any closer!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.81,0:16:44.64,italics,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine as long as\Nyou're not dead, Shindo!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:51.36,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.21,0:16:56.03,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You worked hard today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:58.24,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have more chances tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.45,0:17:02.24,italics,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.24,0:17:03.83,italics,JOTA,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.83,0:17:05.22,italics,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Probably King.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:06.75,italics,KING,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.75,0:17:08.88,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up. Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.88,0:17:12.91,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If you're running tomorrow, stay warm\Nwhile you sleep and don't overeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.91,0:17:13.90,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.90,0:17:14.97,main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,That's all?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.30,0:17:17.64,italics,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have any more helpful advice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:19.26,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.26,0:17:20.35,italics,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.77,0:17:22.30,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be over after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.30,0:17:25.10,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is focus, so we\Ncan give everything we've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.89,0:17:34.36,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. Why don't we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:36.32,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,The mountains of Hakone are?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.18,0:17:42.02,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure yours will feel the most authentic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.02,0:17:43.04,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:52.38,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The mountains of Hakone are?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:54.62,main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,The steepest in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:06.39,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,It might snow tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.16,0:18:08.28,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.17,0:18:10.84,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Was that your parents' idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:13.28,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,You mean my name? Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.28,0:18:15.19,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,My father ran track.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:18.30,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Did your father push you towards running, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.30,0:18:21.16,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,No. Our communication was never...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.16,0:18:23.49,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:32.79,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,My father is a high school track coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.26,0:18:35.05,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I was one of his runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:42.21,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,He's not a bad person.\NHe just loves track to a fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:45.81,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't have time to think\Nwhile under his total supervision,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.81,0:18:48.16,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and I ran every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.16,0:18:50.98,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually, I broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.95,0:19:29.73,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.56,0:19:35.19,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Unable to run for the first time,\NI genuinely wanted to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:51.12,Chikusei_so_19:47(Ep 20),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Chikusei-so
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.32,0:19:53.67,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I'll share a dream with\Nteammates who earnestly want to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.29,0:19:56.29,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Whether they're weak or amateurs,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:01.55,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,as long as they've got talent and\Npassion, I'm sure they can run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:11.34,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,For that, I bent everyone to my will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.48,0:20:18.69,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,We knew there was only ten of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.69,0:20:20.25,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,But we're more than ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.98,0:20:24.27,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,The shopping center vendors, the university,\Nand the people far away from us
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.27,0:20:26.82,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,are all part of the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:29.18,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,No one thinks you forced them to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.18,0:20:34.46,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you did, don't forget\Nthat I'm grateful for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.65,0:20:36.84,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.28,0:20:43.15,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to run the best we ever have.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.38,0:22:45.90,Next_ep_title,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: Goodbye, Beautiful World
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.53,0:22:44.36,main,NARRATION,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, “Goodbye, Beautiful World.”
